<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 300/76 of 9 February 1976 determining the categories of officials entitled to allowances for shiftwork, and the rates and conditions thereof </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, EURATOM) nr 300/76, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks ametnike kategooriad, kellel on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; eest, ning selle h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;rad ja maksmise tingimused 9. veebruar 1976 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Staff Regulations of officials and the conditions of employment of other servants of the European Communities laid down in Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68 (1), as last amended by Regulation (Euratom, ECSC, EEC) No 2577/75 (2), and in particular Article 56a, second paragraph of the said Staff Regulations, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirju ja &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimusi, mis on kehtestatud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (Euratom EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;) nr 2577/75, (2) ja eriti k&otilde;nealuste personalieeskirjade artiklit 56a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission submitted after consulting the Staff Regulations Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse ettepanekut, mille komisjon esitas p&auml;rast n&otilde;upidamist personalieeskirjade komiteega, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is for the Council, acting on a proposal from the Commission submitted after consulting the Staff Regulations Committee, to determine the categories of officials entitled to allowances for shiftwork, and the rates and conditions thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et n&otilde;ukogu &uuml;lesanne on ettepaneku p&otilde;hjal, mille komisjon esitas p&auml;rast n&otilde;upidamist personalieeskirjade komiteega, m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks ametnike kategooriad, kellel on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; eest, ning selle h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;rad ja maksmise tingimused, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> An official paid from appropriations in the research and investment budget and employed in an establishment of the Joint Research Centre or on indirect action, or paid from appropriations in the operational budget and employed in a computer centre, or a security department, and who is engaged in shiftwork within the meaning of Article 56a of the Staff Regulations shall be entitled to an allowance of: - Bfrs 2 685 - where the department operates on a two-shift basis, excluding Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays; </inglise>
<eesti> Personalieeskirjade artikli 56a t&auml;henduses vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;taval ametnikul, kellele makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu teadusuuringute ja investeeringute eelarvest ja kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab Teadusuuringute &Uuml;hiskeskuse asutuses v&otilde;i on h&otilde;lmatud kaudse tegevuse projektiga v&otilde;i kellele makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu tegevuseelarvest ja kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab m&otilde;nes andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluskeskuses v&otilde;i turvaosakonnas, on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist: - 2685 Belgia franki, kui t&ouml;&ouml; toimub kahes vahetuses, v&auml;lja arvatud laup&auml;evad, p&uuml;hap&auml;evad ja riigip&uuml;had; </eesti>
<inglise> - Bfrs 4 430 - where the department operates on a round-the-clock basis, excluding Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays; </inglise>
<eesti> - 4430 Belgia franki, kui t&ouml;&ouml; toimub &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;ev l&auml;bi, v&auml;lja arvatud laup&auml;evad, p&uuml;hap&auml;evad ja riigip&uuml;had; </eesti>
<inglise> - Bfrs 6 041 - where the department operates on a continuous basis. </inglise>
<eesti> - 6041 Belgia franki, kui tegemist on katkestamatu t&ouml;&ouml;protsessiga. </eesti>
<inglise> The allowance shall be adjusted by the weighting applicable to the official's salary. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitisele kohaldatakse ametniku palga suhtes kohaldatavat paranduskordajat. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where shiftwork does not continue throughout the month, one thirtieth of the said allowance shall be paid for each day on which shifts are worked. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ametnik ei t&ouml;&ouml;ta vahetustega kogu kuu, makstakse iga p&auml;eva eest, mil ta tegi vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;d, &uuml;ks kolmek&uuml;mnendik k&otilde;nealusest h&uuml;vitisest. </eesti>
<inglise> However, no allowance shall be paid if the number of days of shiftwork is fewer than three per month. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitist ei maksta, kui vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; kestab v&auml;hem kui kolm p&auml;eva kuus. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> An official who can show that for a period not exceeding one month he was prevented from doing shiftwork on grounds of illness, accident, shutdown, leave for attendance at training courses or annual leave, shall retain his entitlement to the allowance. </inglise>
<eesti> Ametnik, kes suudab t&otilde;endada, et ta ei saanud kuni kuu aega teha vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;d haiguse, &otilde;nnetuse, t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku, koolitusel osalemiseks antud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse v&otilde;i p&otilde;hipuhkuse t&otilde;ttu, s&auml;ilitab &otilde;iguse h&uuml;vitisele. </eesti>
<inglise> If the period during which he is prevented from doing shiftwork extends to more than one month, his entitlement to the allowance shall be suspended at the end of that month until he resumes work. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ajavahemik, mil ta ei saa vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;d teha, &uuml;letab &uuml;hte kuud, peatatakse tema &otilde;igus h&uuml;vitisele k&otilde;nealuse kuu l&otilde;pus seniks, kuni ta taasalustab t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> An official who is entitled to payment of the allowance provided for in Article 1 may receive the allowances for particularly arduous work provided for in Article 100 of the Staff Regulations only up to a maximum of 600 points, to be determined in accordance with Regulation (Euratom) No 1799/72 (3). (1) OJ No L 56, 4.3.1968, p. 1. (2) OJ No L 263, 11.10.1975, p. 1. (3) OJ No L 192, 22.8.1972, p. 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Ametnik, kellel on &otilde;igus artiklis 1 s&auml;testatud h&uuml;vitisele, v&otilde;ib saada personalieeskirjade artiklis 100 s&auml;testatud h&uuml;vitist eriti raske t&ouml;&ouml; eest k&otilde;ige rohkem 600 punkti ulatuses, mis m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ruse (Euratom) nr 1799/72 (3) kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall apply mutatis mutandis to temporary, auxiliary and establishment staff. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse mutatis mutandis ajutiste, abi- ja koosseisuliste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Articles 1 and 4, second paragraph, of Council Regulation (Euratom) No 1371/72 of 27 June 1972 determining the rates and the conditions of the special allowances which may be granted to officials or servants who are paid from appropriations in the Research and investment budget and employed in an establishment of the Joint Research Centre or on indirect action for services of a special nature (1), are repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> Teadusuuringute ja investeeringute eelarvest palka saavatele ja Teadusuuringute &Uuml;hiskeskuse asutuses t&ouml;&ouml;tavatele v&otilde;i kaudse tegevusega tegelevatele ametnikele v&otilde;i teenistujatele eriliste t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete eest makstavate eritoetuste m&auml;&auml;rade ja tingimuste kehtestamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (Euratom) nr 1371/72 (4) artikkel 1 ja artikli 4 teine l&otilde;ik tunnistatakse kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 1 February 1976. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohaldatakse 1. veebruarist 1976. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. Br&uuml;ssel, 9. veebruar 1976 </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 9 February 1976. </inglise>
